<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. M. Tian &amp; N. Jiang" authorityYear="2020" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Valsaceae" genus="Cytospora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Cytospora xinglongensis" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="xinglongensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Cytospora xinglongensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName genus="C." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="C. californica" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="californica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">C. californica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="C." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="C. eucalypti" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="eucalypti">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">C. eucalypti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by longer conidia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Named after the county where it was collected, Xinglong County.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Sexual morph: not observed. Asexual morph: Pycnidial stromata immersed in bark, erumpent through the surface of bark, discoid, with a solitary undivided locule. Conceptacle black, circular surrounded stromata. Ostiole inconspicuous. Locules undivided, circular to ovoid, (480-)540-685(-755) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
diam. Conidiophores hyaline, unbranched. Peridium comprising a few layers of cells of textura angularis, with innermost layer brown, outer layer brown to dark brown. Conidiogenous cells enteroblastic polyphialidic, (4.5-)6.5-8.5(-12) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1-1.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
(x̄ = 7.4 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.3 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
). Conidia hyaline, allantoid, eguttulate, smooth, aseptate, thin-walled, (7.5-)8.5-9.5(-10.5) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1-1.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
(x̄ = 8.9 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.3 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Culture characters.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">On PDA at 25 °C in darkness. Cultures are white. The colony is flat, thin with a uniform texture, lacking aerial mycelium. Pycnidia distributed uniformly on medium surface.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Specimens examined.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
China, Hebei Province, Chengde City, Xinglong County, chestnut plantation, 
<geoCoordinate degrees="40" direction="north" minutes="24" orientation="latitude" precision="15" seconds="32" value="40.40889">40°24'32&quot;N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate degrees="117" direction="east" minutes="28" orientation="longitude" precision="15" seconds="56" value="117.48222">117°28'56&quot;E</geoCoordinate>
, on branches of 
<taxonomicName class="Thecofilosea" family="Castanellidae" genus="Castanea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Chromista" lsidName="Castanea mollissima" order="Phaeocalpida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Cercozoa" rank="species" species="mollissima">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Castanea mollissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 11 October 2017, N. Jiang (
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">holotype</emphasis>
BJFC-S1706, ex-type living culture CFCC 52458; 
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">paratype</emphasis>
BJFC-S1707, living culture CFCC 52459).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. M. Tian &amp; N. Jiang" authorityYear="2020" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Valsaceae" genus="Cytospora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Cytospora xinglongensis" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="xinglongensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Cytospora xinglongensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is associated with canker disease of 
<taxonomicName class="Thecofilosea" family="Castanellidae" genus="Castanea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Chromista" lsidName="Castanea mollissima" order="Phaeocalpida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Cercozoa" rank="species" species="mollissima">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Castanea mollissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in China. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. M. Tian &amp; N. Jiang" authorityYear="2020" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Valsaceae" genus="Cytospora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Cytospora xinglongensis" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="xinglongensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Cytospora xinglongensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from its phylogenetically closely species 
<taxonomicName genus="C." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="C. thailandica" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="thailandica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">C. thailandica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having much longer conidia (8.5-9.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
in 
<taxonomicName genus="C." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="C. xinglongensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="xinglongensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">C. xinglongensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
vs. 3.3-4 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
in 
<taxonomicName genus="C." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="C. thailandica" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="thailandica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">C. thailandica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/mycokeys.38.28011" author="Norphanphoun, C" journalOrPublisher="Mycokeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="93 - 120" refId="B31" refString="Norphanphoun, C, Raspe, O, Jeewon, R, Wen, TC, Hyde, KD, 2018. Morphological and phylogenetic characterisation of novel Cytospora species associated with mangroves. Mycokeys 38: 93 - 120, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/mycokeys.38.28011" title="Morphological and phylogenetic characterisation of novel Cytospora species associated with mangroves." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/mycokeys.38.28011" volume="38" year="2018">Norphanphoun et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
). In addition, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. M. Tian &amp; N. Jiang" authorityYear="2020" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Valsaceae" genus="Cytospora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Cytospora xinglongensis" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="xinglongensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Cytospora xinglongensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName genus="C." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="C. thailandica" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="thailandica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">C. thailandica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by ITS, ACT and RPB2 loci (16/470 in ITS, 22/245 in ACT and 52/726 in RPB2).
</paragraph>
